[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":507},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide\u002F":482,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide\u002F":491},"\u002Fother\u002F20210627\u002F3588736352\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":464,"date":465,"description":466,"extension":467,"lang":468,"meta":469,"navigation":470,"path":471,"readingMinutes":472,"seo":473,"standalone":474,"stem":475,"tags":476,"tldr":479,"updated":479,"url":480,"__hash__":481},"content\u002Fen\u002FMisc\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide.md","robots.txt Quick Guide","6358873625",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":453},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,36,43,46,49,52,58,61,66,73,116,119,123,126,150,154,161,167,170,195,210,213,218,248,251,265,268,277,280,294,299,304,334,341,344,349,358,361,390,393,400,403,412,415,424,427,431,449],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"What does robots.txt actually do, and does it really matter for SEO? Writing down what I know.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"robotstxt","robots.txt",[17,25,26,27,31,32,35],{},"robots.txt is what the name suggests — a plain text file. It lives at your site's root. For example, my site is ",[28,29,30],"code",{},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002F",", so the file would be at ",[28,33,34],{},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Frobots.txt",".",[17,37,38,39,35],{},"Heads up — the filename is ",[40,41,42],"strong",{},"all lowercase",[17,44,45],{},"Its job is to tell crawlers (spiders) which pages they can index and which they shouldn't.",[17,47,48],{},"One thing worth knowing — robots.txt isn't a hard standard. It's a convention. Whether a crawler respects it is up to them, so don't rely on robots.txt to hide sensitive info — it's an opt-out request, not access control.",[17,50,51],{},"From Wikipedia:",[53,54,55],"blockquote",{},[17,56,57],{},"The robots.txt protocol is not a standard, but rather a consensus, so it cannot guarantee a site's privacy.",[17,59,60],{},"That said, Google's docs note:",[53,62,63],{},[17,64,65],{},"On July 1, 2019, Google announced that it was working to make the robots.txt protocol an internet standard. This document has been updated to reflect that.",[17,67,68,69,72],{},"There's another approach — drop a ",[28,70,71],{},"meta"," tag into your HTML telling crawlers not to index or follow links from this page:",[74,75,80],"pre",{"className":76,"code":77,"language":78,"meta":79,"style":79},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cmeta name=\"robots\" content=\"noindex, nofollow\" \u002F>\n","html","",[28,81,82],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,84,87,91,94,98,101,105,108,110,113],"span",{"class":85,"line":86},"line",1,[83,88,90],{"class":89},"sMAXC","\u003C",[83,92,71],{"class":93},"sKpQp",[83,95,97],{"class":96},"sCcAr"," name",[83,99,100],{"class":89},"=",[83,102,104],{"class":103},"sTRMh","\"robots\"",[83,106,107],{"class":96}," content",[83,109,100],{"class":89},[83,111,112],{"class":103},"\"noindex, nofollow\"",[83,114,115],{"class":89}," \u002F>\n",[17,117,118],{},"Same caveat — also a convention, not a standard. So if you really don't want something indexed, the best move is to not put it online.",[12,120,122],{"id":121},"how-to-write-robotstxt","How to write robots.txt",[17,124,125],{},"The common directives:",[127,128,129,135,140,145],"ul",{},[130,131,132],"li",{},[28,133,134],{},"User-agent",[130,136,137],{},[28,138,139],{},"Disallow",[130,141,142],{},[28,143,144],{},"Allow",[130,146,147],{},[28,148,149],{},"Sitemap",[151,152,134],"h3",{"id":153},"user-agent",[17,155,156,157,160],{},"User-agent picks which crawlers a rule applies to. Most sites use ",[28,158,159],{},"*"," (everyone).",[17,162,163,164,35],{},"If you want Google's crawler specifically: ",[28,165,166],{},"User-agent: Googlebot",[17,168,169],{},"Common crawler names:",[127,171,172,177,183,189],{},[130,173,174,175],{},"Google — ",[28,176,166],{},[130,178,179,180],{},"Yahoo — ",[28,181,182],{},"User-agent: Slurp",[130,184,185,186],{},"Bing — ",[28,187,188],{},"User-agent: bingbot",[130,190,191,192],{},"Baidu — ",[28,193,194],{},"User-agent: Baiduspider",[17,196,197,198,200,201,203,204,206,207,35],{},"Think of ",[28,199,134],{}," as a \"group\" — it usually pairs with ",[28,202,139],{}," or ",[28,205,144],{},". It's required in robots.txt, but the most common is just ",[28,208,209],{},"User-agent: *",[151,211,139],{"id":212},"disallow",[17,214,215,217],{},[28,216,139],{}," tells crawlers which paths to skip. WordPress example — typically you'd block the admin paths:",[74,219,223],{"className":220,"code":221,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"language-txt shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","User-agent: *\nDisallow: \u002Fwp-admin\nDisallow: \u002Fwp-includes\nDisallow: \u002Fwp-content\n","txt",[28,224,225,230,236,242],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,226,227],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,228,229],{},"User-agent: *\n",[83,231,233],{"class":85,"line":232},2,[83,234,235],{},"Disallow: \u002Fwp-admin\n",[83,237,239],{"class":85,"line":238},3,[83,240,241],{},"Disallow: \u002Fwp-includes\n",[83,243,245],{"class":85,"line":244},4,[83,246,247],{},"Disallow: \u002Fwp-content\n",[17,249,250],{},"You can also block duplicate URLs — category pages, tag pages, etc.:",[74,252,254],{"className":220,"code":253,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"User-agent: *\nDisallow: \u002Farchives\u002F\n",[28,255,256,260],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,257,258],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,259,229],{},[83,261,262],{"class":85,"line":232},[83,263,264],{},"Disallow: \u002Farchives\u002F\n",[17,266,267],{},"After that, URLs like this won't get indexed:",[74,269,271],{"className":220,"code":270,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Farchives\u002F\n",[28,272,273],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,274,275],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,276,270],{},[17,278,279],{},"To block crawlers from indexing the entire site:",[74,281,283],{"className":220,"code":282,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"User-agent: *\nDisallow: \u002F\n",[28,284,285,289],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,286,287],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,288,229],{},[83,290,291],{"class":85,"line":232},[83,292,293],{},"Disallow: \u002F\n",[295,296,298],"h4",{"id":297},"block-specific-files","Block specific files",[17,300,301,303],{},[28,302,139],{}," can also block specific file types:",[74,305,307],{"className":220,"code":306,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"User-agent: *\nDisallow: \u002F*.gif$\nDisallow: \u002F*.js$\nDisallow: \u002F*.inc$\nDisallow: \u002F*.css$\n",[28,308,309,313,318,323,328],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,310,311],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,312,229],{},[83,314,315],{"class":85,"line":232},[83,316,317],{},"Disallow: \u002F*.gif$\n",[83,319,320],{"class":85,"line":238},[83,321,322],{},"Disallow: \u002F*.js$\n",[83,324,325],{"class":85,"line":244},[83,326,327],{},"Disallow: \u002F*.inc$\n",[83,329,331],{"class":85,"line":330},5,[83,332,333],{},"Disallow: \u002F*.css$\n",[17,335,336,337,340],{},"Heads up — ",[40,338,339],{},"don't block JS, CSS, or font files",", or you'll get warnings in Google Search Console (Google can't render your pages properly without them).",[151,342,144],{"id":343},"allow",[17,345,346,348],{},[28,347,144],{}," is the opposite — explicit allow paths. Most sites set this to everything:",[74,350,352],{"className":220,"code":351,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"Allow: \u002F\n",[28,353,354],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,355,356],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,357,351],{},[17,359,360],{},"For my blog I also explicitly allow some paths:",[74,362,364],{"className":220,"code":363,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"Allow: \u002F\nAllow: \u002Farchives\u002F\nAllow: \u002Fcategories\u002F\nAllow: \u002Ftags\u002F\nAllow: \u002Flinks\u002F\n",[28,365,366,370,375,380,385],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,367,368],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,369,351],{},[83,371,372],{"class":85,"line":232},[83,373,374],{},"Allow: \u002Farchives\u002F\n",[83,376,377],{"class":85,"line":238},[83,378,379],{},"Allow: \u002Fcategories\u002F\n",[83,381,382],{"class":85,"line":244},[83,383,384],{},"Allow: \u002Ftags\u002F\n",[83,386,387],{"class":85,"line":330},[83,388,389],{},"Allow: \u002Flinks\u002F\n",[151,391,149],{"id":392},"sitemap",[17,394,395,396,399],{},"Sitemap is non-standard too — it points crawlers at your site's ",[28,397,398],{},"sitemap.xml",". Major search engines all support it.",[17,401,402],{},"Setup is just pointing at the URL:",[74,404,406],{"className":220,"code":405,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"Sitemap: \u003Chttp:\u002F\u002Fwww.example.com\u002Fsitemap.xml>\n",[28,407,408],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,409,410],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,411,405],{},[17,413,414],{},"For my blog:",[74,416,418],{"className":220,"code":417,"language":222,"meta":79,"style":79},"Sitemap: https:\u002F\u002Fisraynotarray.com\u002Fsitemap.xml\n",[28,419,420],{"__ignoreMap":79},[83,421,422],{"class":85,"line":86},[83,423,417],{},[17,425,426],{},"Final reminder — robots.txt isn't a magic switch. Whether crawlers follow it is up to them.",[12,428,430],{"id":429},"references","References",[127,432,433,442],{},[130,434,435],{},[436,437,441],"a",{"href":438,"rel":439},"https:\u002F\u002Fen.wikipedia.org\u002Fwiki\u002FRobots.txt",[440],"nofollow","robots.txt (Wikipedia)",[130,443,444],{},[436,445,448],{"href":446,"rel":447},"https:\u002F\u002Fdevelopers.google.com\u002Fsearch\u002Fdocs\u002Fadvanced\u002Frobots\u002Frobots_txt",[440],"Robots.txt Specifications (Google)",[450,451,452],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .sKpQp, html code.shiki .sKpQp{--shiki-default:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sTRMh, html code.shiki .sTRMh{--shiki-default:#ADDCFF}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":79,"searchDepth":232,"depth":232,"links":454},[455,456,457,463],{"id":14,"depth":232,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":232,"text":23},{"id":121,"depth":232,"text":122,"children":458},[459,460,461,462],{"id":153,"depth":238,"text":134},{"id":212,"depth":238,"text":139},{"id":343,"depth":238,"text":144},{"id":392,"depth":238,"text":149},{"id":429,"depth":232,"text":430},"Misc","2021-06-27 17:05:43","Quick note on what robots.txt actually does, why it matters for SEO, and how to write one. Covers the basic directives (User-agent, Disallow, Allow, Sitemap), the most common crawler User-agents, and the important caveat — robots.txt is a convention, not a guarantee, so don't rely on it to hide sensitive info.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide","3",{"title":6,"description":466},false,"en\u002FMisc\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide",[477,478],"robots","SEO",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Frobots-txt-quick-guide\u002F","tRBno4WA5-_Goh8IXw6J5aN2IefDVtXXGi3PIqiEME8",{"newer":483,"older":487},{"url":484,"title":485,"date":486},"\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F30\u002Fgithub-password-auth-brownout-fix\u002F","Fixing 'Password authentication is temporarily disabled as part of a brownout'","2021-06-30 17:23:37",{"url":488,"title":489,"date":490},"\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2021\u002F06\u002F27\u002Fvue3-two-way-binding-concept\u002F","Vue 3 Two-Way Binding: Concept and Implementation","2021-06-27 13:56:44",[492,497,502],{"url":493,"title":494,"date":495,"readingMinutes":496},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F06\u002F23\u002Fmac-stats-menu-bar-system-monitor\u002F","Stats — The Free Open-Source macOS Menu Bar System Monitor I Use Every Day (CPU, GPU, Temperature, Network)","2026-06-23 10:00:00","5",{"url":498,"title":499,"date":500,"readingMinutes":501},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F26\u002Fhow-much-does-a-blog-really-earn-with-google-adsense\u002F","Can a Blog Really Make Tens of Thousands of Dollars a Month? Real Google AdSense Numbers, Explained","2026-05-26 21:00:00","6",{"url":503,"title":504,"date":505,"readingMinutes":506},"\u002Fen\u002Fmisc\u002F2026\u002F05\u002F18\u002Fvscode-disable-integrated-browser-auto-open\u002F","VSCode Opens Every Link in the Integrated Browser? How to Disable Auto Takeover","2026-05-18 14:30:00","4",1784012780423]